{
  "stem": "27770.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, there was a big brick factory in Munkacs. and this was the place, the central, where the trains came in from the outside, because usually they used to ship with the trains the bricks.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we had to-- first they made a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The ghetto became two or three times smaller and smaller.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And by the end, all the Jews got taken out from the little villages all around the town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then they took us from the ghetto to this brick factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We heard a lot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, I with my father used to listen from London the news, BBC.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Officially, we couldn't hear it, because everybody had to bring to the city his radio.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They was putting a stamp on it, and there was only one station was available Budapest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So you couldn't hear nothing, just the news from Hungary, whatever they were interested we should listen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But came a mechanic, a radio mechanic, and he told me, Schlesinger, to my father, I'll show you how to you could listen it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's very dangerous.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If they catch you, you are next day already in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They send you to forced labor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So be very careful before you listen this news.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Close up all over the doors, and nobody should know about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he showed us there is a little string in the radio that the button was the way they stamped left there, but we was pulling the string here and there and came evening 9:00, and we heard bum bum bum boom, bum bum bum boom.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was from London.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They did not let us know from London that you go to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They did not let us know from the [NON-ENGLISH] from Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They take you to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
